snippet.textDisplay:
Riley: [knocks on Hacksmith's door] "Hacksmith?"
Hacksmith: "Yeah, can I help you?"
Riley: "This is Riley, from LMG."
Hacksmith: "Oh, hello, Riley."
Riley: "Linus installed some stuff for you guys awhile back and wanted me to check in with you guys to see if it was operating alright. Can I come in and do a quick inspection? Five minutes, tops."
Hacksmith: "Sure, that's awfully nice of Linus to send someone out to make sure our stuff is working right."
[sometime later]
Hacksmith: "Hey, has anyone seen the lightsaber?"
Hacksmith crew: "Yeah, we all worked on it together, remember?"
Hacksmith: "No, I mean has anyone seen it lately?'
Hacksmith crew: "No."
[cut to darkened room, a figure in dark robes opens up a long box. He reaches in and pulls out the lightsaber. He lifts it up and ignites the blade, the reflection bouncing off the glasses on the man's face. He turns and addresses another man sitting on his lower legs. The second man, a hood obsuring his upper face, leaving only his dark beard to be seen.

Riley: [channeling Palpatine] "Arise my...servant. It is time...the moment for our revenge is at hand. Go to the LMG Temple and do what must be done..."
James: "Yes, my Master..."

[James walks into the upper level of the LMG Temple. Youngling Col-Tan approaches him, timidly]

[saber ignites]

[Col-Tan jerks in surprise]
 
[saber swish]

[Fade to black]

[Riley leans back from workstation and takes a swig from his water bottle. LTTstore.com He shakes his head and holds down the delete button.]

Riley: "That's a bit too quick bitty, even even me..."

James [reading over shoulder]: "Aww, I was just starting to like it..."
